  "description": [
    "4 Russia Fights for the United Nations WM The CIO NEWS September 20 1943 Organized workers of the whole country had to hang their heads in shame when the organ of one of the largest American unions the International Teamster launched a venomous attack on our Soviet ally in its September issue Its leading editorial entitled Russia Fights Only for Russia was joyfully republished by the antilabor commercial press The articles revives the ancient lie that it was the Russian treaty with Germany that Unionists In Service Bro Iinne Stlerstorfer an old member of 1874 from Textile is missing in action following a raid over Ualy July 17 lie was a slafT sergeant of the 95th Bombardment Squadron Bro Wm Joseph Andres of Erk hart whose mother sister and brother have also been members of Local 1874 was killed at Canip 1 lowe Tex as the result of an accidental shooting Bro Lyle T Howdyshell from Textile who joined Local 1874 in im and later was captured by the Japs in the Philippines writes his parents that he is in excellent health Bro Roy Brtink of the Twisting Dept a member of 1874 since 1941 and Bro August Robertson of"
